 are actually honored.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The LLM re-ranking step changes the order of at least some results compared to the raw similarity ranking when the query has nuanced intent.","minimum_level":"Agentic","test_description":"Execute the full search pipeline with a nuanced query (e.g., 'budget-friendly espresso machines under $300' where similarity ranking may not reflect price sensitivity), capture the initial vector-based ranking, send those results to the real LLM with a reranking prompt, and verify that the final ranking differs from the initial ranking in at least some positions.","justification":"LLM reranking effectiveness depends on what a real, non-deterministic language model produces. A mocked LLM response (even carefully crafted) cannot validate that the actual model understands nuanced intent or that the prompt engineering elicits appropriate reordering. Real LLM output is required to catch cases where the prompt fails or the model misinterprets intent.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A query with no close matches in the database returns an empty result set rather than low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Integration","test_description":"Run a query against a test vector database with a query far outside the corpus domain (e.g., query about 'nuclear reactor design' in a fashion product database), configure a similarity threshold (e.g., cosine similarity > 0.7), and verify that the API returns an empty result set with zero items, not low-scoring results.","justification":"Similarity score ranges and threshold behavior are vector database-specific and depend on real embedding distributions. A mock might use unrealistic score ranges, causing threshold logic to be tested incorrectly. A test database with real data shows whether the filtering threshold logic works correctly with actual similarity distributions.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The end-to-end latency from receiving the query to returning re-ranked results stays below 2 seconds for the median case.","minimum_level":"Workflow","test_description":"Execute the complete search pipeline 100+ times with real embedding model, real vector database, and real LLM re-ranking. Measure total latency from query receipt to final re-ranked result. Calculate p50 latency and verify it stays below 2 seconds. Include realistic network conditions and ensure the LLM inference cost is accounted for.","justification":"Latency measurement requires all real components working together: embedding model (Agentic), vector database (System), and LLM re-ranking (Agentic). Testing embedding and LLM separately or in pairs would miss orchestration overhead, network round-trip costs, and the cumulative delay of the full pipeline. Only a complete workflow test shows whether the end-to-end SLA is met.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.48}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13550,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13550},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac467c2b-21bd-4f28-88bb-2e5c52194fc8","uuid":"57152aa5-d159-419a-bf30-3544d360d35a"}
